parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid is leaking from the brake lines
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brake pedal to push back against the foot, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system engages at low speeds
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal pushes back against the foot
the vehicle is unable to stop
the ABS light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds. This can increase the risk of accidents, and the subsequent loss of power to the steering and braking systems can further compromise safety.
symptoms: The fuel pump quits working while driving
causing a loss of power
stalling
or failure to start; inaccurate fuel level readings
including sudden drops to empty; fuel leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust fumes to enter the cabin of the vehicle, leading to driver drowsiness or illness, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Exhaust manifold bolts snapping off
exhaust fumes entering the cabin
driver feeling sleepy or sick from the fumes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to decelerate when the accelerator pedal is released can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle fails to decelerate when the accelerator pedal is released
vehicle continues to accelerate unintentionally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coolant connector can cause hot coolant to escape, potentially leading to burns, injuries, or accidents.
symptoms: Engine coolant connector failure
hot coolant escaping
risk of burns or injuries.
